===Etymology===
From {{etyl|goh|de}}. The first part has absorbed the tribal name [[Angle]], and an extended form of the god's name [[Ing]] (as in [[Ingela]]), and was in Christian times interpreted as {{term|Engel||an angel|lang=de}}. The second part is {{term|beraht||bright|lang=goh}}. Popularized by a martyred 13th century bishop of [[Cologne]].

